description:
&lt;p&gt;The Dietetic Service are looking to recruit a Team Manager to oversee our Adult and Paediatric Services at East Cheshire NHS Trust. This provides an excellent opportunity to join our friendly, proactive service including 15 Dietitians covering both hospital and community , 3 dietetic assistants and 3 part –time Administrators with the support of a Band 7 Home Enteral feeding Dietitian/Community Team Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will mainly involve team management however a proportion of the role will be clinical preferably in Paediatric Dietetics. The current paediatric service covers Paediatric home tube feeding, Children’s diabetes, general out-patient clinics and some in-patient work. The post holder would be part of an enthusiastic dietetic team with strong links to wider community services including community and specialist nurses , including those in Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires strong leadership skills, a high level of communication and interpersonal skills to support staff and for MDT working, patient education on a one to one and in a group setting and health care professional training. Ideally you will have a broad dietetic experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service is committed to the training of student dietitians and other health care professionals. The department encourages innovation and supports continuous professional development. We are utilising electronic record keeping and mobile working across the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jo Derbyshire Job title Operational Manager AHP Email address jo.derbyshire@nhs.net Telephone number 01625 661881&lt;/p&gt;
